{"questionId":"19656","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/54071ea9c5563debdb6c44ca39d1600b8a1c4f58.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>&nbsp;is defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>, stating its domain.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>M1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong>M1</strong> for interchanging <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> (can be done at a later stage).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>domain is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Correct alternative notations include&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>]</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>∞</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>]</mo></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>∞</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>]</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[5 marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19656","referenceCode":"EXN.1.SL.TZ0.8c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find an expression for f-1x, stating its domain.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.2—Functions, notation domain, range and inverse as reflection","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Composite functions, identity, finding inverse"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}